title: Georgia House - Day 13 (2026-11-19)
summary:
# Georgia House - Day 13 (2026-11-19)

## Overview
This session was relatively brief, with no substantive legislation being passed or introduced. The majority of the time was spent on procedural matters and brief remarks.

## Key Actions
No bills were passed or referred during this session.

## Bills Introduced (First Reading)
- **SB 2EX**: Relating to the composition and number of congressional districts, and legislative and congressional reapportionment.

## Notable Moments
The session consisted primarily of the House coming to order, the clerk reading the first reading of a Senate bill, and the House adjourning until the next scheduled session on November 20th at 9 AM.

## Votes
No recorded votes were taken during this session.

## Attendance
A quorum was present, as the House was able to conduct business.

## Adjournment
The House adjourned at the conclusion of the session and will reconvene on November 20th at 9 AM.
